<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_SP49_CrystalCreations_GemologySkills" s="360182">
  <T n="name">0xC56D9700<!--Gemology Skill--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP49\UI\Tutorial\CrystalCreations_GemologySkills_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fb4ce816bb4daeb9</T>
      <T n="text">0x7CBBD168<!--Design and craft your own <b><font color='#199C2C'>custom Jewelry</font></b> and cut dazzling <b><font color='#199C2C'>Gemstones</font></b> with the Gemology Skill. Decorate your Sims and their homes, make buckets of Simoleons, and discover the hidden power of crystals!\n\nAll you need to get started is <b><font color='#199C2C'>The All-In-One Gemology Table By Humphrey Inc.</font></b> from the Creative subcategory under Activities and Skills in Build Mode.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP49\UI\Tutorial\CrystalCreations_GemologySkills_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fb4ce816bb4daeba</T>
      <T n="text">0x58AD92E7<!--Select <b><font color='#199C2C'>Design Jewelry</font></b> on the Gemology Table to start making your own Jewelry. Customize it by selecting a design, a metal, and a crystal (if applicable).\n\nTo make Gemstones, select <b><font color='#199C2C'>Cut Gemstones</font></b> on the Gemology Table, and combine a cut with a crystal.\n\nIncrease your Sim's Gemology Skill to <b><font color='#199C2C'>unlock</font></b> new Jewelry designs and Gemstone cuts.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP49\UI\Tutorial\CrystalCreations_GemologySkills_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fb4ce816bb4daebb</T>
      <T n="text">0x69C8F2CA<!--If the <b><font color='#199C2C'>ingredients</font></b> chosen are available in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>inventory</font></b> of the Sim or the Gemology Table, they will be used in the crafting process. This <b><font color='#199C2C'>reduces the crafting cost</font></b>.\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Common and uncommon</font></b> crystals and metals that your Sim doesn't already have can be bought directly in the crafting menu. <b><font color='#199C2C'>Rare</font></b> crystals and metals have to be acquired beforehand to craft with them.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP49\UI\Tutorial\CrystalCreations_GemologySkills_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fb4ce816bb4daebc</T>
      <T n="text">0x28FECD96<!--You can find Crystals and Metals by <b><font color='#199C2C'>digging at rocks</font></b> found across the Neighborhoods. The areas around the Parks in Oasis Springs and Willow Creek are great places to start!\n\nOnce your Sim reaches Gemology Skill level 3, they can cut a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Crystal Seed</font></b> and plant it to grow a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Crystal Tree</font></b>. The more you take care of and evolve the tree, the rarer Crystals it will produce!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP49\UI\Tutorial\CrystalCreations_GemologySkills_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fb4ce816bb4daebd</T>
      <T n="text">0xD16734BF<!--You can make a pretty Simoleon by selling crafted Jewelry and Gemstones! Their value depends on the <b><font color='#199C2C'>unlock level</font></b> of the design, the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Quality</font></b> of the piece, and the <b><font color='#199C2C'>rarity</font></b> of the crystal and metals used.\n\nSims that are in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Focused</font></b> mood have a higher chance of creating high Quality pieces.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP49\UI\Tutorial\CrystalCreations_CrystalCharging_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4247d1535764141b</T>
      <T n="text">0x7C2774D8<!--Both Gemstones and Jewelry can be <b><font color='#199C2C'>charged</font></b> to unlock their innate powers! Check out the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Crystal Charging</font></b> lesson to learn more.--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_SP49_CrystalCreations</E>
  </L>
</I>